A car crashed into Glasgow Airport, engulfing the terminal in flames.
Witnesses described a 4X4 vehicle rammed into the building, sparking chaos.
British Prime Minister Gordon Brown confirmed it as a terrorist attack, raising security levels.
The incident followed a foiled car bomb plot in London.
Authorities closed airports and heightened security measures.
Two suspects were arrested in connection with the attacks.
The burning car at Glasgow Airport was linked to the London incidents.
The nation remained on high alert, with public vigilance urged.
The situation underscored the ongoing threat of terrorism.
